verbose_text: In HEK293 cells transfected with HOIL-1, His-V5-HOIP, and UBE2L3, cells gated for high co-production of V5 tagged HOIP and UBE2L3 showed a substantial shift in the percentage of cells showing p65 nuclear translocation (39.9%), whereas no significant shift in p65 translocation (10.7%) was observed in cells with normal HOIP and UBE2L3 levels within the same sample (XREF_FIG D and 2E).
